1
00:00:48,583 --> 00:00:50,666
[OPERATOR 4A] The mobile suit
squad has been wiped out!


2
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:51,541
But how?


3
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:53,458
There was only one unit!


4
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:59,958
So that's what Metus is
swingin' around these days.

5
00:01:00,041 --> 00:01:02,000
What the hell's wrong
with you, Subaru?

6
00:01:02,083 --> 00:01:03,666
Get back here.

7
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,583
[CALLAWAY]
Mr. Isuzu?

8
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:14,333
For some reason,
I knew you'd be here.

9
00:01:14,416 --> 00:01:16,000
Good for you.

10
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:18,791
You know I don't approve
of entering enemy territory

11
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:20,708
during a test flight.

12
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:22,833
Yes, I'm sorry.

13
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,583
But... I wasn't
afraid of injuries.

14
00:01:25,666 --> 00:01:28,291
I figured if I could at
least make you smile,

15
00:01:28,375 --> 00:01:30,041
it would be worth it.

16
00:01:30,125 --> 00:01:33,250
[ISUZU] Yeah, because I love
pilots with death wishes.

17
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:34,666
Whatevs.

18
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:37,500
Can't copy those with artificial
Universe Sense, anyway.

19
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:39,375
Uh. Sorry.

20
00:01:39,458 --> 00:01:41,708
I'm not mad at you, okay?

21
00:01:41,791 --> 00:01:44,125
A drink for the lady, please.

22
00:01:44,208 --> 00:01:45,916
[BARTENDER 4A]
You got it, boss.

23
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,833
[cocktail shaker rattles]

24
00:01:50,375 --> 00:01:51,875
Ever had a gimlet?

25
00:01:51,958 --> 00:01:54,583
It matches the color
of your eyes perfectly.

26
00:01:54,666 --> 00:01:56,500
Oh, how fancy!

27
00:01:56,583 --> 00:01:58,375
You should name your mecha that.

28
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:01,125
In commemoration of
your premier battle.

29
00:02:01,208 --> 00:02:03,125
That's a good idea.

30
00:02:03,208 --> 00:02:04,750
[ISUZU]
Take Subaru B.

31
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,500
His senses haven't
fully developed yet.

32
00:02:07,583 --> 00:02:09,958
He was put on
the field too soon.

33
00:02:10,041 --> 00:02:12,375
I won't make that
mistake again with you.

34
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:14,708
I feel confident that
you're ready to fight.

35
00:02:14,791 --> 00:02:16,125
And I'm glad you're safe.

36
00:02:16,208 --> 00:02:18,041
Thank you, sir.

37
00:02:19,375 --> 00:02:21,833
[CALLAWAY] You saw something
in me when I was nothing.

38
00:02:21,916 --> 00:02:24,041
You're the one who
brought me this far,

39
00:02:24,125 --> 00:02:26,958
and for that, I will
always be grateful.

40
00:02:27,041 --> 00:02:29,000
Ready to close out, boss?

41
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:31,916
[NARRATOR]
After he returned from Earth...

42
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,291
[ISUZU]
Yes, I think so.

43
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:36,125
And we'll be paying separately.

44
00:02:36,208 --> 00:02:37,625
[NARRATOR]
Isuzu learned to budget

45
00:02:37,708 --> 00:02:39,541
even when it made
things awkward.

46
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:40,625
[CALLAWAY]
Seriously...?

47
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:42,291
[ISUZU]
I'll take a receipt for mine.

48
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:45,041
[CALLAWAY] I just came in to
report on my battle results.

49
00:02:45,125 --> 00:02:48,125
<i>He's</i> the one who
ordered the damn drink.

50
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,375
[CALLAWAY gasps]

51
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:53,625
[CALLAWAY] I thought only
children had Velcro wallets?

52
00:02:53,708 --> 00:02:55,166
I always pictured Mr. Isuzu

53
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:58,583
with a classic, crocodile skin
billfold, but maybe this one

54
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:01,916
holds sentimental value
from his childhood?

55
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,250
[BARTENDER 4A]
All right, miss, here you go.

56
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:05,750
[CALLAWAY]
It was just one drink.

57
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,000
It can't be more than--

58
00:03:07,083 --> 00:03:10,083
[BARTENDER 4A]
One gimlet plus nuts... 1580.

59
00:03:10,166 --> 00:03:11,500
[CALLAWAY]
What nuts?!

60
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:13,875
I didn't even eat any nuts!

61
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:16,666
[ISUZU] Go ahead and put
all the points on this card.

62
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:18,666
[CALLAWAY]
He's stealing the points?

63
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:20,541
[CALLAWAY groaning]

64
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:22,416
[CALLAWAY]
I'm fine. I won't hate Mr. Isuzu

65
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,916
over a drink and some
nuts I didn't even want!

66
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,333
It's fine!

67
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:30,083
[CALLAWAY grunts]

68
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:32,916
I didn't realize she was
such a lightweight.

69
00:03:37,375 --> 00:03:38,916
What happened?

70
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,958
Well, look who's sober.

71
00:03:41,041 --> 00:03:42,583
Where are we?

72
00:03:42,666 --> 00:03:44,583
[ISUZU] The Kerukeionm,
where it's awesome!

73
00:03:44,666 --> 00:03:46,541
Rest here as long as you need.

74
00:03:46,625 --> 00:03:48,458
You brought me
to your cockpit?

75
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:50,250
[stomach growls]

76
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:52,708
[ISUZU]
I heard that.

77
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:55,291
You shouldn't be drinking
on an empty stomach.

78
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:57,375
I guess I should've
asked if you'd eaten.

79
00:03:57,458 --> 00:03:59,375
Here. These are good.

80
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:05,875
[CALLAWAY]
He cares!

81
00:04:05,958 --> 00:04:07,458
Oh. Wait.

82
00:04:07,541 --> 00:04:11,416
[NARRATOR] It was December
of Space Age 0157.

83
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:14,041
Is it cool if I grab
the sticker from it first?

84
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:16,583
[NARRATOR] And Isuzu was
still a miserly tool.

85
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:18,375
I think I just need three more.

86
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,250
You send in the points and
they give you one of those

87
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:22,166
cute bunny plates.

88
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,375
Oh, yeah?

89
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:25,208
How fun for you...

90
00:04:25,291 --> 00:04:26,875
[NARRATOR]
'Twas the night before Subaru

91
00:04:26,958 --> 00:04:28,458
was launched back into space.

92
00:04:28,541 --> 00:04:32,583
A small assist bot was stirring,
from a decision she'd made.

93
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:35,000
She left a note and
said her goodbyes.

94
00:04:35,083 --> 00:04:38,125
It would be hard to depart
from the hero's side.

95
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:39,291
And scene.

96
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:41,666
[PAC2-AR]
Please take care, Mr. Subaru.

97
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,333
Since you've found
newer equipment,

98
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:46,250
there's no connecter
I can interface with.

99
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:49,708
I'm just an obsolete
robot to you now.

100
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,833
[PAC2-AR] But I've always
wondered what it would be like

101
00:04:52,916 --> 00:04:55,125
to sit here and yank
on this lever thingie!

102
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:56,666
[NARRATOR]
In case there was any question,

103
00:04:56,750 --> 00:05:00,375
PAC2-AR's mentality was like
that of an eight-year-old child.

104
00:05:00,458 --> 00:05:01,791
[PAC2-AR]
Check me out sortieing in

105
00:05:01,875 --> 00:05:03,583
the Neo Durandal like a beast!

106
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:05,875
Boop, beep, boink, beep!

107
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:07,208
[PAC2-AR laughs]

108
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:09,666
Huh? Uh-oh, did I
turn something on?

109
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:11,000
[PAC2-AR gasping]

110
00:05:13,166 --> 00:05:15,833
Welcome and Greetings
from Lexus2000,

111
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:18,208
the Neo Durandal's AI.

112
00:05:18,291 --> 00:05:20,208
[PAC2-AR]
I didn't mean to wake you up.

113
00:05:20,291 --> 00:05:21,458
It's all right.

114
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:24,375
But you do not appear
to be Subaru Ichinose.

115
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,166
In which case, I hope
you don't mind,

116
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:28,666
but I'd like to air
a few complaints.

117
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:31,208
[PAC2-AR] Sure. Let's talk
about your feelings.

118
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,625
[LEXUS2000]
It's Subaru.

119
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:35,041
Once he realized I was
his personal mecha,

120
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:37,666
he started slapping
me with stickers.

121
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:40,041
And well, I don't like it.

122
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:43,041
[PAC2-AR]
Huh. Sounds like he was sharing

123
00:05:43,125 --> 00:05:45,416
his playful side with you.

124
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:47,875
C'mon, Lex, an advanced
program such as yourself

125
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,125
doesn't let stuff like
that get to him, right?

126
00:05:50,208 --> 00:05:52,166
Why not, I'm an AI?

127
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:55,041
Any entity capable of
thought can become upset.

128
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:56,625
We're programmed...

129
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:58,375
[PAC2-AR] Wow, so if great AIs
with majestic character design

130
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:02,041
can have problems,
then I'm doin' all right.

131
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:07,000
Ah... It feels like
my battery's dyi--

132
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,666
[SUBARU]
Wakey-Wakey!

133
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:14,375
Can't waste the day
in sleep mode.

134
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:15,833
[PAC2-AR]
Subaru...?

135
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,166
--[SUBARU] Hm?
--[PAC2-AR gasps]

136
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:18,166
[SUBARU]
Uh?

137
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:19,333
[PAC2-AR]
Where's Lex?!

138
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:21,291
I don't know what that means.

139
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:23,458
Is that someone from Dream Town?

140
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:26,000
[PAC2-AR]
Oh. Maybe it was?

141
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,333
[PAC2-AR]
I forgot about that. Subaru, I--

142
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:32,541
[SUBARU] And what's with
the dramatic break-up note?

143
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:35,250
I don't care if you can't
connect well with the interface.

144
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:38,166
Who'll be my lil cockpit
buddy if you go?

145
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,500
[PAC2-AR]
You really mean that?

146
00:06:43,083 --> 00:06:44,416
Subaru.

147
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:47,583
I need your help, not
as a pilot, but as a...

148
00:06:47,666 --> 00:06:49,000
...as an Ichinose,

149
00:06:49,083 --> 00:06:51,416
please bring that
powder puff back home.

150
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:54,333
Already on it, Papa.

151
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:58,791
[NARRATOR]
In December of Space Age 0157,

152
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:02,250
Subaru and PAC2-AR made
their return to space.

153
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:05,875
[SOICHIRO]
Hmm, there it is again.

154
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:08,000
This song keeps getting
stuck in my head.

155
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:09,458
[SUBARU]
The Durandal song?

156
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,708
Yeah, I'll be step touch and
snappin' to it in my head

157
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:13,708
even when the captain
is yelling at me.

158
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:15,708
[SOICHIRO]
It's only the best song ever.

159
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:17,583
[SUBARU]
Oh, it's like a one hit wonder!

